<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-544-798  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 544 798.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  June 4 1990 v218 n23 p28(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A powerful problem for local loop fiber. (powering optical networkunits)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Coleman, John D.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Southwestern Bell Telephone analyzed the safety, cost andreliability issues connected with the various power architecturemodels for optical network units (ONU).andP;  Network power, localpower and hybrid solutions were considered.andP;  Network power,involving placement of an overlay copper network or use of theexisting copper network for dispatching power to the ONU, wasfound to be very expensive.andP;  Moreover, the power levels involvedcould jeopardize employee and public safety.andP;  Local power viaaccess to a power source on a subscriber's premises would bepreferable in terms of cost and safety, and is the choice ofSouthwestern Bell.andP;  Battery backup for each ONU may be required.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Southwestern Bell Telephone Co. (research).andO;Topic:     Fiber opticsTelephone companiesNetworksTelecommunications.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>